news.title: Chandigarh: Sector 29 homes to have house number indicator boards soon
news.para: Area councillor Shakti Parkash Devshali pushed the case on the demand of residents. The MC has decided to put up similar boards in the entire city.

news.title: No question of protecting anyone in BDA corruption: Karnataka CM
news.para: ​The Anti-Corruption Bureau (ACB), on Friday had raided the BDA office here and claimed to have unearthed irregularities and corruption by officials during acquisition and allotment of land in residential layouts.

news.title: IT department detects Rs 100-crore black income after raids on Gujarat group
news.para: "...incriminating evidences in the form of documents, diary notings and digital data showing earning of huge unaccounted income by the group and its investment in assets have been seized," the CBDT said in a statement.

news.title: Why insolvency cases are giving Noida & Greater Noida authorities a tough time
news.para: While the GNIDA is dealing with 21 cases of insolvency proceedings before the National Company Law Tribunal and the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal, the Noida Authority is party to 16 such resolution cases or appeals, at present.

news.title: Tamil Nadu RERA appoints panel to execute sale deeds of 700 buyers
news.para: ​The Rera authority will write to the country planning department for permission; then the association will apply for registration with Rera and the homebuyers’ body will complete the project.

news.title: Zirakpur: 70 allottees get third FIR registered against GBP builders
news.para: Members of the management of Gupta Builders and Promoters (GBP) Group left the country without completing real estate projects, leaving 2,500 investors who had invested around Rs 1,500 crore two months ago, in the lurch.

news.title: Gurugram: BPTP Astaire Garden residents say builder failed to fulfil promise
news.para: ​The residents alleged that the society does not have permanent electricity connection as a result they have been facing frequent power cuts and voltage fluctuation.

news.title: Covid pandemic affects Kochi corporation's property tax collection
news.para: In the absence of a proper system for tax collection, revenue generation has been affected. Arrears to the contractors would come to around Rs 100 crore.

news.title: Over 1 lakh people get homes in Praygraj district under PMAY, MMAY
news.para: ​Of these, while 1,14,189 people have been benefited under PMAY, 8569 people have been helped under MMAY since 2016.

news.title: Mumbai: With CRZ washed away, steep curve ahead for Pali Hill skyline
news.para: A massive construction boom is on the anvil at prime seafront locations in the city, especially between Bandra and Versova, after Coastal Regulation Zone (CRZ) norms were diluted by the Centre recently.

news.title: Government puts MTNL, BSNL real estate assets worth about Rs 970 crore on sale
news.para: BSNL properties located in Hyderabad, Chandigarh, Bhavnagar and Kolkata have been posted for sale at a reserve price of around Rs 660 crore.

news.title: Bengaluru: ACB seize land records worth Rs 100 crore from BDA offices
news.para: The raids were conducted on BDA on Friday later in the noon and continued till late night. ACB confirmed that the raids were continuing on Saturday and the BDA officers will be inquired and questioned based on the evidence gathered.

news.title: China's land sales slump 13.14% in October as property woes worsen
news.para: The value of government land sales in October declined 13.14% from a year earlier to 573.7 billion yuan ($89.90 billion), after suffering a drop of 11.15% in September, according to Reuters calculations of data released by the finance ministry on Friday.

news.title: IT department detects Rs 200-crore black income after raids on Kolkata group
news.para: The department seized Rs 1.30 crore cash and placed half-a-dozen bank lockers, unearthed during the raids, under restraint, The Central Board of Direct Taxes (CBDT) said.

news.title: Bhopal Metro to start by September 2023: Madhya Pradesh CM
news.para: Madhya Pradesh Metro Rail Corporation Limited is implementing the metro project in Bhopal and Indore. Two metro corridors are being built in Bhopal from AIIMS to Karond square and from Bhadbhada square to Ratnagiri square.
